'FC Dinamo Minsk' (; , FK Dynama Minsk) is a professional football club based in
the Belarusian capital city of Minsk. It was founded in 1927 as part of the
Soviet Dinamo Sports Society. Dinamo Minsk is the only club from the
Byelorussian SSR that competed in the Soviet Top League, playing 39 of the 54
seasons, and winning the title in 1982. Since the independence of Belarus the
club participates in the Belarusian Premier League, having won 7 league titles
and 3 Belarusian Cups. Dinamo plays its home games in the 4,500 capacity Dinamo-
Yuni Stadium .
